From: "Barak A. Pearlmutter" <barak@pearlmutter.net>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 23:36:49 +0100
Subject: Do not pass null pointer to std::string::append in Backtrace::get()

std::string::append has undefined behavior when its pointer argument is null.
Remove the null argument; a subsequent push_back already appends the same
character.  Fixes a build failure with gcc 15, which turns this UB into a
trap.
---
 src/Backtrace.cc | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/Backtrace.cc b/src/Backtrace.cc
index bee80ff..beec15b 100644
--- a/src/Backtrace.cc
+++ b/src/Backtrace.cc
@@ -327,7 +327,6 @@ std::string tmp;
    tmp.reserve(result_max + 1);
    for (const char * b = buf; *b &&  b < (buf + result_max); ++b)
        tmp += *b;
-   tmp.append(0);
 
 char * e = 0;
 int status = 3;
